Dominik Marczuk 11 ay önce •
Great idea for a simple DIY project when you're learning JavaScript. On the technical side though, I'd make sure the DOM is traversed as few times as humanely possible. In your implementation, the ISBN number of the removed book is fetched from the content of a sibling td element. Now, imagine someone decides to change the structure of the HTML template. It would all stop working. And the more places in your code where you traverse the DOM, the more changes you'll need to introduce. Instead, I'd add the ISBN number as a data attribute to the button. That way, no DOM traversing would be needed and you would be free to e.g. change from a table display to a list or a grid of divs or whatever.
